<content>
        
    
BANGKOK (Reuters) - Thailand's PTT Exploration and Production PTTE.BK said it was looking at BP's (BP.L) assets in Vietnam but has not appointed financial advisers for any plan to bid for them.

"We are interested in BP's assets because it is in our target area, both in Vietnam and Southeast Asia," Chief Executive Anon Sirisaengtaksin told Reuters. He gave no details.BP (BP.L) has said it planned to sell its stake in the Nam Con Son project, part of its goal of selling $30 billion in assets over the next 18 months to cover costs for containing the oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico.($1 = 31.95 Baht)(Reporting by Pisit Changplayngam; Writing by Khettiya Jittapong; Editing by Alan Raybould)


